{
  "doc_id": "21801",
  "text": "Qualitative RT-PCR analysis of eggs, white-eyed pupae, adult bees and body parts of adult bees for the presence of DWV was performed essentially as already described. Total RNA was extracted using an RNeasy kit (Qiagen) following the manufacturer's protocols [CITATION_1] . Eluted RNA (50 ml) was stored at 270 uC for subsequent analysis. One-step RT-PCR was performed according to standard protocols (OneStep RT-PCR kit; Qiagen) as previously described [CITATION_2] , using the primer pair F1/B1 (F1, 59-CCTGCTAATCAACAAGGAC-CTGG-39; B1, 59-CAGAACCAATGTCTAACGCTAACCC-39) resulting in a DWV-specific amplicon of 355 bp [CITATION_3] .",
